<configuration>
  <!--
    SkiaSharp's LibraryLoader declares [DllImport("dl")] to call dlopen/dlsym
    on Linux. Mono's default dllmap for 7D2D V2's bundled runtime doesn't
    remap the short name "dl" to "libdl.so.2", so the DllImport fails with
    "dl assembly:<unknown assembly>" and SkiaSharp.SKData's static constructor
    throws — taking MapTileRenderer (and anything else that touches Skia) down.

    A per-assembly .dll.config sitting next to SkiaSharp.dll is the canonical
    Mono fix for this: it registers the dllmap in the scope of this assembly's
    DllImports only, no system config edits needed.
  -->
  <dllmap dll="dl" target="libdl.so.2" os="!windows" />
</configuration>
